doc.after: By 1990 Embraer engineers found that results from wind tunnel testing were less than satisfactory and began considering a significantly different design from the EMB 120 The proposed modified design included a slightly 22 3 swept wing with winglets as well as engines mounted in underwing nacelles This second design showed markedly better aerodynamic performance but the combination of swept wings and wing mounted engines required an unusually high and therefore heavy undercarriage 2
